Coming into the shop, I found that it was very clean and spacious. It was a holiday (they close early) but I found ample room to sit and chat with my friend. The environment had enough ambient noise to feel like a cafe but quiet enough to actually have a good conversation with someone.  Looking at the menu, I see that over half prices were covered, which was very strange to me. I didn't mind that the prices "changed," but it was annoying how I couldn't tell how much a simple bagel with lox was.  Although the menu did say "Flavored Iced Tea," when I asked for it, the staff was confused as to what the flavors were. There seems to be a disconnect between what was written in the back where the menu was and what the place actually served.  I ordered a simple iced coffee. It was not the best coffee I ever had but it was decent for the hot afternoon. I wouldn't come back to the store just for the coffee. I do want to come back to try the bagels there.  In the end, I found the cafe to be very clean and spacious. It is a great place to grab a quick drink and sit for a while with friends. The windows are clear so you can watch the people walk down Atlantic. Although the menu situation is confusing, I wouldn't mind coming back for another go.
